
;
NUMBER 1359
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 82
MINEB
REGION 2
;MONSTER_GROUP 87
NAME Deep Realms, rock tunnel
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A small stream emerges from behind a rock on the tunnel wall here. It meanders slowly along the passage for a few feet, and disappears again into a crack. Small eyeless white fish swim against the light current without moving forward. The movemnet of the water makes a pleasant babbling sound.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 1358
EXIT NW 1361
EXIT E 1364
ITEM 0 426
PUT 0 198 VAL2=100
PUT 0 380 ADJ1=347
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Their little mouths open and close rythmically as if they were idly hoping a small meal might just float in.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	ECHO PLAYER "Babble babble," goes the brook.
ENDIF
IFTOUCH -1
	IFVAR ARCHNUM = 380
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You try to catch the fish but they deftly swims out of your hand.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR RAC = 3
		ECHO PLAYER This is Kinderhunt. Somewhere down the endless cracks and crevices is where the mite riders keep their herds of rock mites. Though not very daunting as an enemy, they would take over Kragenholm if they could. For whatever reason they are not content to just live side by side with the deeplanders or anybody. Perhaps it is their small size, but their huge egos keep them constantly on the plotting. Its best to not give them a good chance to get started.
	ELSE
		IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
			ECHO PLAYER This is Kinderhunt. Somewhere down the endless cracks and crevices is where the mite riders keep their herds of rock mites. Though not very daunting as an enemy, they would take over Kragenholm if they could. For whatever reason they are not content to just live side by side with the deeplanders or anybody. Perhaps it is their small size, but their huge egos keep them constantly on the plotting. Its best to not give them a good chance to get started.
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
