NUMBER 1351
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
CHANNEL 82
REGION 2
;MONSTER_GROUP 87
NAME Home
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A typical deeplander home, there is a simple wooden table in front of a large stone fireplace. The gem studded walls are stone too as the room has been hewn directly from the rock of the Deep Realms. Outsiders are sometimes stunned by the sheer volume of gems deeplander live with everyday. What they wouldn't guess was the the most valuable item in the room to a highlander family was the wooden table -- there are no trees in the Deep Realms.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 1371
ITEM 0 91 ADJ1=539 ADJ2=355
ITEM 1 195 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=312
PUT 1 196
PUT 0 373
IFPREVERB OUT -1
	IFVAR INTNUM6 = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER Ooops, you were so excited you forgot to grab your torch off the table.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GET -1
	IFVAR ARCHNUM = 373
		EQUAL INTNUM6 0
		NEWPUT 0 373
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY
	EQUAL INTNUM6 1
	EQUAL INTNUM80 5
	ECHO PLAYER You find yourself at home. Looking around you see your family is not around at the moment. This is good as you all hate long good-byes. As a going away present they all chipped in and donated to the temple five times in your name. You have chosen the way of an adventurer, and although you will be in and around Kragenholm, you will never be a child in this house again. For you, the world is outside now.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1360
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 82
MINEA
REGION 2
NAME Bat cave entrance
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A gigantic carvern opens up in front of you. The smell here is nearly
unbearable. The stench emanates from the thick black goo that covers the
floor. Holding your light up so that its glow reaches the ceiling you see
that it moves. Billions of bats cling to its every surface. Their
catawalling squeals are nearly deafening. The stinking black goo below is
guano. A shattered outcropping of rock is all that's left of the stairway
of rock that led into the depths. You see below you a massive amount of
store where the area caved in.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1358
ITEM 0 706
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR RAC = 3
		ECHO PLAYER You remember the tales your family told about the bat cave. As a young adventurer you should probably stay out of there until you are well trained, or rich enough to pay a lot of bills for healing.
	ELSE
		IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
			ECHO PLAYER You have heard that the bat cave is not an adventure for those just off their mother's apron strings.
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
